Class InventoryItem

java.lang.Object
com.inFlight.shared.model.InventoryItem
public class InventoryItem extends Object
InventoryItem is a class that represents an item in the inventory. It contains information about the item ID, name, condition, availability, owner role, and checkout status. POJO (Plain Old Java Object) class.

  • Constructor Details

    • InventoryItem

      public InventoryItem(int id, String name, String condition, boolean available, String ownerRole, boolean checkedOut)
      Constructor to create an InventoryItem object with specified ID, name, condition, availability status, owner role, and checkout status.
      Parameters:
      id - the ID of the item
      name - the name of the item
      condition - the condition of the item
      available - the availability status of the item
      ownerRole - the role of the owner ("Photographer" or "Attendant")
      checkedOut - the checkout status of the item

    • InventoryItem

      public InventoryItem(String name, String condition, boolean available, String ownerRole)
      Constructor to create an InventoryItem object with specified name, condition, availability status, and owner role. The ID is set to -1 and the checkout status is set to false by default.
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the item
      condition - the condition of the item
      available - the availability status of the item
      ownerRole - the role of the owner ("Photographer" or "Attendant")
